Fix for https://github.com/ncsa/oa4mp/issues/218. Changed package and some class names related to virtual issuers.
RFC 6749 §4.4 documentation, client credentials flow
https://github.com/ncsa/oa4mp/issues/221, https://github.com/ncsa/oa4mp/issues/222
https://github.com/ncsa/oa4mp/issues/219, https://github.com/ncsa/oa4mp/issues/216 (more VO renaming of internal variables to vi)
https://github.com/ncsa/oa4mp/issues/219, https://github.com/ncsa/oa4mp/issues/216 (more VO renaming of internal variables to vi)
https://github.com/ncsa/oa4mp/issues/225, https://github.com/ncsa/oa4mp/issues/224, https://github.com/ncsa/oa4mp/issues/222, https://github.com/ncsa/oa4mp/issues/221
https://github.com/ncsa/oa4mp/issues/224, https://github.com/ncsa/oa4mp/issues/225, https://github.com/ncsa/oa4mp/issues/226
https://github.com/ncsa/oa4mp/issues/224, https://github.com/ncsa/oa4mp/issues/225, https://github.com/ncsa/oa4mp/issues/226
documentation updates
documentation updates
Playing catchup to 6.0.2
Missing file
https://github.com/ncsa/oa4mp/issues/228 Improve error messages from QDL modules so scripts give more detailed messages.
Rebuild of website, fixed a few issues with PDFs, added index.html for https://jira.ncsa.illinois.edu/browse/CIL-2143 and https://github.com/ncsa/oa4mp/issues/229

Official support for RFC 8707: https://www.rfc-editor.org/rfc/rfc8707
We accept this at all points of the flow already. What the RFC outlines is, in effect, that the server should implement policies based on the resources server. Since OA4MP is not tied to any resource server, this is normally done on a per client basis as part of the policy for that client.
https://github.com/ncsa/oa4mp/issues/243 side effect of https://github.com/ncsa/security-lib/issues/45
https://github.com/ncsa/security-lib/issues/46 fallout for https://github.com/ncsa/oa4mp/issues/232
website update
Mostly formatting updates in the CLI to support result set printing.
While chasing down formatting errors, got tired of doing the same 4 queries repeatedly to test, and created https://github.com/ncsa/oa4mp/issues/245 which wonderfully streamlines it.
Failing test needed slight tweak (turned out to be wrong phase in the client configuration, but a few minor mods were made along the way).

https://jira.ncsa.illinois.edu/browse/CIL-2231 fallout. Changes to FNAL's LDAP for the cilogontest user broke several existing tests, so as part of comprehensive testing, these were rewritten and improved.
https://github.com/ncsa/oa4mp/issues/246 LDAP errors not quite getting propagated back to the QDL layer.
Integrating fixes for 6.1.0
Changes reflecting https://github.com/ncsa/qdl/issues/123. All tests working as per requirements.
Side effect of of better value management in QDL has exposed a few potential NPEs. Fixed.
https://github.com/ncsa/oa4mp/issues/249 removed old functor engine. This was a very simple-minded configuration format in JSON that was replaced by QDL.
Needed to update create table QSL scripts.
Removing dead code.
Restructuring for https://jira.ncsa.illinois.edu/browse/CIL-2249.
Before removing functors
https://github.com/ncsa/oa4mp/issues/250 Last vestiges of the Verifier including the tests
Before moving MyProxy stuff

https://jira.ncsa.illinois.edu/browse/CIL-2249 https://github.com/ncsa/oa4mp/issues/254 Isolate old MyProxy code into its own Maven module. In the future, OA4MP instances that need MyProxy can just use that module.
Getting webapp to actually deploy witht he right dependencies, part 2 of https://jira.ncsa.illinois.edu/browse/CIL-2249 https://github.com/ncsa/oa4mp/issues/254
Removing unused webapp modules, part 3 of https://jira.ncsa.illinois.edu/browse/CIL-2249 https://github.com/ncsa/oa4mp/issues/254
Checkin before intergrating changes from https://github.com/ncsa/security-lib/issues/55
More fallout from improving bootstrap sequence in command line utilities. Found some issues in the QDL storage module. Wrote basic Pelican startup scripts.
https://jira.ncsa.illinois.edu/browse/CIL-2278 Added regression tests to check that a revoked admin client stops all flows and access dead.

https://github.com/ncsa/oa4mp/issues/260 removing old TX record tests. They are failing now thanks to a library change, but they are testing a serialization format we abandoned long ago, so reviving them is really just not worth it.
Checkin before release
https://github.com/cilogon/cilogon-java/issues/58 and streamlined creation of NCSA LDAP configuration stems. Integrating 6.2.0 changes
Routine checkin. Added a test, tweaked a few others.
Routine checkin. Added a test, tweaked a few others.
Port of CILogon DBService to OA4MP.
